<br>
Beyond the rules however, EE also operates on a 'spirit' of NBG. Thus, each member considers thoughtfully whether the item in question is truly an upgrade for him, or if it is a better upgrade for someone else who is present. If you don't know, feel free to ask.<br>
<br>
Once you have won a piece of loot, do not roll again until all eligible have won something.<br>
<br>
Spells &amp; Parchments:<br>
Spells will be awarded to the highest level person present who can sit and scribe the spell on the spot. Ties will be randomed. If no one is high enough level, the spell will be given to the highest level person available who needs the spell. Overflow may go to the guildbank or may be distributed or sold as cash loot.<br>
Parchments will be randomed among all the casters one level below the spell level and above (i.e. ethereal parchements for 61 &amp; 62 level spells will be rolled on by 60+, spectral parchments by 62+, etc.). Winners will drop out of succeeding rolls until all have recieved a parchement.<br>
<br>
Cash loot in an EE group is usually disposed of two ways: If the item has a lot of value to the PC community but will not be used by anyone present, it is randomed as cash loot. Typically those who have won items under NBG do not participate in this roll. Other cash loot is sold at a vendor and split evenly among the group members, after reimbursing the cleric for buff gems.<br>
<br>
Cash loot on raids is to be delivered to the Raid Leader to cover the costs of raiding. By custom, blue diamonds are rolled on and diamonds are distributed to wizards on Hate raids, but raid leader discretion prevails.<br>
<br>
ROLLING: EE uses a seeded roll on a 200 random. Each person /rand 200, then the seeder will /rand 200. The closest person to the seed wins the roll.<br>
<br>
Epic Loot Drops:<br>
EACH MEMBER IS RESPONSIBLE for posting their epic progress including dates on the Epic Quest forum. <br>
The person at the event closest to completion of the epic as posted in the EE Epic Forums will be awarded the drop.<br>
If two people have the same number of steps to completion, the one who has been waiting longer (within EE) will be awarded the part. <br>
If both have been waiting the same number of months the drop will be randomed between them.<br>
<br>
Targetted raids for specific epic drops are completely permissible. If you need Phinny for one of his many drops, for instance, and camp him and muster the forces for him and fight him and he drops it, it is yours.<br>
<br>
Exceptions to Epic Drops:<br>
Some droppable epic pieces will be guild banked and handed on an as-needed last-item basis, such as jade reavers.<br>
<br>
Guests: Guests are eligible for all rolls, but will not be considered for epic drops unless no EE need the drop.<br>
<br>
Alts: We do not distinguish between alts &amp; mains. Whoever is there is eligible for whatever drops for his/her class. <br>
